messages.message: I can take a look at this today as well, and I was wondering if my account could be given access to these project workspaces (<mailto:pauline.comising+aihubprod@instabase.com|pauline.comising+aihubprod@instabase.com>) or what admin account can be used to see :woman-bowing::skin-tone-2: when I use the one-pass commercial org admin creds, I still don't have access.
<mailto:pauline.comising@instabase.com|pauline.comising@instabase.com> is already an org admin in “Instabase” and should be able to access this project and app

Thanks! using that account, I've created my own app for both projects, the original and the duplicate and I wasn't able to replicate, rather I saw:
• app runs correctly extracting ID Number
• build runs also ERRORing on Expiration date
I'll run a couple more times to see the consistency of this app run behavior, but if either of you are able to consistently get wrong values, I think publishing the app will give me access you your runs and soln accuracy sets
@pauline.comising I have shared this app (https://aihub.instabase.com/hub/apps/4eedf2b3-228c-4d5e-b4b9-f1aaff5f6925) with the rest of the IB org so you should be able to access the runs

Ah thanks, hmm I only see the one I just ran, created in my workspace with fields that extracted correctly :pensive: is it possible that as org admin, I don't have access to the workspaces you're running in?

i think the UI only shows you runs in workspaces that you. have explicit access to (not workspaces that you can implicitly access as an org admin)

@david.lee i think we’ll need direct links to your app runs to be able to view those results

@pauline.comising for example, here’s my app run (https://aihub.instabase.com/review/9472c923-f3c6-4bc1-b650-79bdd8c9fc21) with the incorrect “ID Number” for NYID1.pdf and the `ERROR` “Expiration date” for RAC3 Report.pdf
